<PageLayout title="Sprocket — Doubling App Sign-ups in 3 Months | Emily Backes" description="Sprocket is a concept app for reporting stolen bikes and flagging suspicious resale listings. I led the full UX process from research through a high-fidelity prototype." ogImage="/assets/cs/sage/662ad570421ba9e8a98b25bc_og-eb-logo.png" bodyBg="#ebe9f0">
<div class="cs-port-root">
<section class="sprocket_hero__section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_hero__container w-container"><div class="cs_hero__heading__wrapper"><h1 class="heading-42">How I doubled expected <br/>registration and app <br/>sign up in 3 months<br/></h1><div class="text-block-35"><strong>Sprocket</strong>: A native, mobile first application for reporting missing bicycles.<br/></div></div><div class="cs_hero__image__wrapper"><div><img class="sprocket_hero__img_one" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14.webp" height="500" alt="sprocket hero landing image" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 248px" data-w-id="83e14e3e-2443-3f15-9c98-6169957e541e" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14-p-500.webp 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14-p-800.webp 800w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14-p-1080.webp 1080w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14-p-1600.webp 1600w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66141d62f690fbd575ae99a8_iPhone 14.webp 1800w"/></div><div class="div-block-136"><img class="sprocket_hero__img_two" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66156ccfc0df66ab31f94ae5_sprocket_search_list.avif" height="500" alt="sprocket hero search image" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 248px" data-w-id="021f7caf-18f1-89f1-5f94-6d37fd72d73f" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/66156ccfc0df66ab31f94ae5_sprocket_search_list-p-500.avif 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66156ccfc0df66ab31f94ae5_sprocket_search_list-p-800.avif 800w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66156ccfc0df66ab31f94ae5_sprocket_search_list.avif 1800w"/></div><div><img class="sprocket_hero__img__three" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66156d3a1c18edba3de6aa3b_sprocket_single_listing.avif" height="500" alt="sprocket hero stolen bike image" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 248px" data-w-id="09c98b03-21a6-34a5-2248-91bfeb93a8ca" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/66156d3a1c18edba3de6aa3b_sprocket_single_listing-p-500.avif 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66156d3a1c18edba3de6aa3b_sprocket_single_listing-p-800.avif 800w, /assets/cs/sprocket/66156d3a1c18edba3de6aa3b_sprocket_single_listing.avif 1800w"/></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_backstory__section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_qi__container w-container"><div class="sprocket_bs__content"><div class="sprocket_story__wrapper"><div class="sprocket_tools__title">how it started</div><h2 class="heading-43"><strong class="bold-text-6">The Backstory</strong><br/></h2><div class="text-block-39">In 2017, Ryan H., the founder of Sprocket came home one day to find his garage had been <strong>broken</strong> into and his bike was <strong>stolen</strong>.</div><div class="text-block-40">After looking for a recovery community, what he discovered was a convoluted, intricate network of social media groups devoted to stolen bikes. </div><div class="text-block-41">Ryan reached out to me to consult on the design of Sprocket.</div></div><div class="sprocket_tools__wrapper"><div class="sprocket_tools__title">UX / UI Skillset leveraged</div><div class="sprocket_pill__wrapper"><div data-w-id="6786e0fc-acbb-f5f8-aaa9-0aae188e4622" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Competitive Analysis</div><div data-w-id="40f0e3ab-ec41-6c5a-d318-8c042d0a50a6" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Research</div><div data-w-id="396ed1be-3edc-268f-90b5-cafca3fc793b" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">wireframes</div><div data-w-id="5f765073-52ca-5847-04d1-3c163ff415f0" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">prototypes</div><div data-w-id="a493d4b0-2a25-9add-f04f-0228226d173d" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Surveys</div><div data-w-id="815b3e92-f274-5757-4774-4ecf9bffea93" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Personas</div><div data-w-id="82c614ba-af8f-ca6f-b2f3-324bf799aff2" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Priority Mapping</div><div data-w-id="9fa87eca-07d7-a94a-7530-f87fd25c20fb" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">mockups</div><div data-w-id="dff752d7-dc6e-f7ef-6f7b-a9fb50e404b2" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Unmoderated testing</div><div data-w-id="f9ced3c3-22b1-4d1b-18c0-8c0d25978e0c" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">Sketching</div><div data-w-id="d30a8a2a-fe20-e6ba-3c74-c96116a68892" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">User Interviews</div><div data-w-id="efc1ba87-c791-4d47-545e-38ceee66cac4" class="default_pill-2 cs_pill">User flows</div></div><div class="sprocket_tools__list"><div class="sprocket_tools__title">Tools Used for Sprocket</div><div class="ux_tools__wrapper"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/65ff30f1590d4325671e194a_Slack Logomark 1.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" height="40" class="ux_tools_logo"/><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6615e52e8367addf238ef114_Loom.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" height="40" class="ux_tools_logo"/><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/65ff30f14bf5714c0727d94c_Google Calendar Logomark 1.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" height="40" class="ux_tools_logo"/><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/65ff2f932a7ab8b822cdf03e_Notion Logomark 1.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" height="40" class="ux_tools_logo"/><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/65ff30f7b6d7ec1b27f59edb_Miro Logomark 1.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" height="40" class="ux_tools_logo"/></div></div></div></div><div class="sprocket_bs__stats"><div class="div-block-82"><div class="w-layout-grid grid-15"><div data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad919" class="div-block-76"><div class="lottie-animation-6" data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad91a" data-animation-type="lottie" data-src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6616c1e39bc779c38087d9ea_wired-outline-500-fingerprint-security (1).json" data-loop="1" data-direction="1" data-autoplay="1" data-is-ix2-target="0" data-renderer="svg" data-default-duration="1" data-duration="3" data-loading="eager"></div><div class="text-block-43"><strong>73%</strong> of bikes stolen at street level were <strong>reported locked </strong>by owners.</div></div><div id="w-node-_22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad922-51521bfe" data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad922" class="div-block-75"><div class="lottie-animation-5" data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad923" data-animation-type="lottie" data-src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6616bf3978287dc5762d7dbb_wired-outline-1985-police-car.json" data-loop="1" data-direction="1" data-autoplay="1" data-is-ix2-target="0" data-renderer="svg" data-default-duration="3" data-duration="3" data-loading="eager"></div><div class="text-block-43"><strong>154,009</strong> bikes were reported stolen in the U.S. in 2019 according to the FBI.</div></div><div data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad928" class="div-block-77"><div class="lottie-animation-7" data-w-id="22074214-cb33-964f-7632-0a8c225ad929" data-animation-type="lottie" data-src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6616cb993d5ffed65c2fbe13_wired-outline-56-document.json" data-loop="1" data-direction="1" data-autoplay="1" data-is-ix2-target="0" data-renderer="svg" data-default-duration="1.4833333333333334" data-duration="0" data-loading="eager"></div><div class="text-block-43">An <strong>estimated 80%</strong> of US bike theft <strong>victims</strong> don’t report the crime to the police.</div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_challenges__section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_challenges__container w-container"><div class="challenge_content__wrapper"><div class="challenge_content"><div class="text-block-44">mind maps &amp; market research</div><h2 class="heading-44"><strong class="bold-text-7">The Client Challenge<br/></strong></h2><div class="text-block-45 client_first__par">In a time when smartphones are ubiquitous, there is no <strong>native</strong> mobile report and recovery solution for missing and stolen bikes. <br/></div><div class="text-block-45">I spent this phase doing market <strong>research</strong>, and <strong>gap</strong> discovery of the products similar to product.  <br/></div></div><div class="challenge_graphics"><div class="text-block-45">After an exhaustive market research, I found that the current competing products lack elements in four different areas: <strong>availability</strong> in the US, a <strong>native</strong> mobile app, stolen bike <strong>feed</strong>, and <strong>messaging</strong> capabilities. <br/></div><div class="text-block-44 research_sh">competitive analysis</div><img class="image-38" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b5f683233a9d9129a342_bikeapp_table_right.avif" width="575" alt="sprocket app comparison" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 575px" data-w-id="0816c925-9c3c-533a-ef37-903b13556136" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b5f683233a9d9129a342_bikeapp_table_right-p-500.png 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/6618b5f683233a9d9129a342_bikeapp_table_right.avif 800w"/><div class="text-block-45"><strong>Mind mapping</strong> is one of my favorite techniques when it comes to UX <strong>research</strong> &amp; <strong>ideation</strong>. It gives me an early glimpse on possible application architecture(s), without heavy cognitive load.<br/></div><div class="text-block-44 research_sh">connecting the dots</div><img class="image-35" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6619867e94ef58afdae7d115_Mind_map_Sprocket-removebg-preview.avif" width="Auto" alt="sprocket mind map" sizes="100vw" data-w-id="6491436a-808a-e861-5dea-81cb06d041da" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/6619867e94ef58afdae7d115_Mind_map_Sprocket-removebg-preview-p-500.png 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/6619867e94ef58afdae7d115_Mind_map_Sprocket-removebg-preview.avif 559w"/></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_ux__section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_ux__container w-container"><div class="sprocket_ux__wrapper"><div class="sprocket_ux__content"><div class="text-block-44">user research</div><h2 class="heading-45">The UX Process</h2><div class="text-block-48 ux_first_par">This was a <strong>full-scope research and design project</strong>. I conducted comprehensive discovery and research including competitive analysis, interviewing and surveying users, empathy mapping, and feature prioritization.</div><div class="div-block-89"><div class="text-block-48 ux_second__par">The key takeaway is that valuable knowledge on how to prevent bike theft is scattered online and not readily available to all cyclists. This lack of awareness leaves them vulnerable:</div><div data-w-id="23b69010-4869-27fc-041e-564331beaec6" class="div-block-88"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b86e1f4d79a6c7d2ea8a_arrow-right-circle.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-33"/></div><div class="text-block-49">They don&#x27;t know how to check if a used bike is registered stolen</div></div><div data-w-id="85ad26d3-7964-3191-0cd0-327e8047a0d6" class="div-block-88"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b86e1f4d79a6c7d2ea8a_arrow-right-circle.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-33"/></div><div class="text-block-49">They&#x27;re unsure how to report a stolen bike</div></div><div data-w-id="b686ddf4-33fa-f5bb-a4d2-e42fcf7faa6e" class="div-block-88"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b86e1f4d79a6c7d2ea8a_arrow-right-circle.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-33"/></div><div class="text-block-49">They lack documentation of purchase or serial numbers</div></div><div data-w-id="fcf6d64a-96d7-5000-928c-a1e513e62bf5" class="div-block-88"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618b86e1f4d79a6c7d2ea8a_arrow-right-circle.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-33"/></div><div class="text-block-49">Cyclists don&#x27;t know where to register their bikes</div></div></div></div><div class="sprocket_ux__graphics"><img class="image-34" src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618435100604be7e91ce50a_simple_user_flow.webp" width="546" alt="sprocket unregistered user flow" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 546px" data-w-id="c369e038-52f3-9652-c8fe-2d3a940825f2" loading="lazy" srcset="/assets/cs/sprocket/6618435100604be7e91ce50a_simple_user_flow-p-500.webp 500w, /assets/cs/sprocket/6618435100604be7e91ce50a_simple_user_flow-p-800.webp 800w, /assets/cs/sprocket/6618435100604be7e91ce50a_simple_user_flow.webp 1092w"/><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/661be4499457b5f44ff99b1e_user_flow_2.avif" loading="lazy" width="478.5" alt="sprocket registered user flow" data-w-id="373884af-501a-a447-6bed-50ae00b44760"/></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_iteration_section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_it__container w-container"><div class="sprocket_it__wrapper"><div class="div-block-91"><div class="text-block-51">Where research &amp; design intersect</div><h2 class="heading-46">Iterate &amp; Conquer</h2><div class="text-block-50">I use a &quot;start loose, finish tight&quot; approach when it comes to design iteration with Sprocket. I also brainstorm in, <strong>mind maps</strong>, <strong>outlines</strong> before diving into any design software, or <strong>sketching</strong> layouts on my iPad before any high-fidelity mockups.</div><div class="text-block-52">This initial looseness lets me explore freely, change direction easily, and avoid tunnel vision. I also find that sketching is also a <strong>low consequence</strong> avenue for <strong>exploration</strong>. </div><div class="text-block-53">After ideation, I let user testing, both <strong>un-moderated</strong> &amp; <strong>moderated</strong>, informed my final design choices, based on user feedback.</div></div><div class="div-block-92"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/661a0401cd2040ad662d49db_Itteration_Wave_2.svg" loading="lazy" data-w-id="0860ba69-2825-0a7d-0297-bf923e3a543b" alt="Start loose, finish tight design principle" class="image-42"/></div></div><div class="sprocket_it__screens"><div class="text-block-51">design evolution through iteration</div><div class="w-layout-grid grid-16"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/661985791a9ee593ebe17993_1_wireframe.avif" loading="lazy" alt="sprocket initial sketch design" height="504" class="image-37"/></div><div id="w-node-_331dd1b9-462a-ea0d-4e10-1cce7dfa81b4-51521bfe"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/661985a2bb7a0aedc9d539a0_2_lofi.avif" loading="lazy" width="Auto" height="504" alt="sprocket low-fidelity design" class="image-71"/></div><div id="w-node-bc0b7183-4bba-89d9-ead8-4fd769741177-51521bfe"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/6619870878fc3580879ea364_3_midfi.avif" loading="lazy" alt="sprocket mid-fidelity design" height="504" class="image-72"/></div><div id="w-node-_76798430-750a-8304-d170-a1c07b89c392-51521bfe"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/661987196cd193297a30d5db_4_hifi.avif" loading="lazy" alt="sprocket high-fidelity design" height="504" class="image-73"/></div></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_ui__section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_ui__container w-container"><div class="sprocket_ui__wrapper"><div class="sprocket_sol__text"><div class="text-block-54">real problems require real solutions</div><h2 class="heading-47">The Solution</h2><div class="text-block-55">I helped turn the client’s vision, a comprehensive, navigable mobile theft and mitigation platform, into a reality. The end result provided a simple, unique solution for the client.</div><div class="text-block-57">We expected <strong>1,500 registrations</strong> and signups in the first 3 months and <strong>received double that. </strong></div><div class="text-block-58">We predict that getting buy-in from universities, police departments, and bike retailers helped Sprocket signup and adoption rates.</div></div><div class="sprocket_sol__image"><div class="div-block-137"><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea670e0df99fdfe4802_sprocket_1.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea7a9cb15de7172d7fc_sprocket_2.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea7cbde1b35d4113160_sprocket_3.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div></div></div><div class="sprocket_ui sprocket_ui__items"><div class="div-block-164"><div class="text-block-111">High Fidelity screens</div></div><div class="div-block-163"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea7d2fd20334eece77a_sprocket_6.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea7e5149972fe00bf44_sprocket_4.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea7e797828d6ef1b6dc_sprocket_9_2.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea79898f8e6250fbcc8_sprocket_9_1.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div></div></div><div class="sprocket_ui"><div class="div-block-163"><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea76ca2859b5800f460_sprocket_9.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea689f572636f1de331_sprocket_7.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea68d8761f8d4ee9f71_sprocket_9_3.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea6d874e65ef415c6f2_sprocket_9_4.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div><div><img src="/assets/cs/sprocket/66426ea6cd4b99a17c5bd738_sprocket_5.avif" loading="lazy" width="196.5" alt="Sprocket app"/></div></div></div></div></section><section class="sprocket_lessons__learned"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer sprocket_lessons__container w-container"><div class="sprocket_lessons__wrapper"><div class="sprocket_lessons__heading"><div class="text-block-54">plans are great, until they change</div><h2 class="heading-47">Challenges </h2></div><div class="lesson_card_wrapper"><div class="sprocket_lesson_card lesson_card_one"><div class="lottie-animation-22" data-w-id="968a30aa-f095-e458-c7e3-3da26b3391a8" data-animation-type="lottie" data-src="/assets/cs/sprocket/662536c7cddfb288d45c1b3b_wired-outline-1534-paper-boat_sprocket.json" data-loop="1" data-direction="1" data-autoplay="1" data-is-ix2-target="0" data-renderer="svg" data-default-duration="3" data-duration="6" data-loading="eager"></div><div class="text-block-87">project challenges</div><div class="text-block-88">Having previous familiarity with existing bike registration applications, I had to identify my own design biases to ensure I wasn’t replicating existing solutions </div></div><div class="sprocket_lesson_card lesson_card_two"><div class="lottie-animation-22" data-w-id="f3f3b0f1-1211-87dc-718a-0fcfc71db961" data-animation-type="lottie" data-src="/assets/cs/sprocket/662537b0817115fff466fa3d_wired-outline-12-layers_sprocket.json" data-loop="1" data-direction="1" data-autoplay="1" data-is-ix2-target="0" data-renderer="svg" data-default-duration="1.5" data-duration="4" data-loading="eager"></div><div class="text-block-87">project changes</div><div class="text-block-88">I didn’t take accessibility into account from the beginning. Some of my elements weren’t ADA-compliant, and I could have used a contrast checker to avoid wasted time and resources.</div></div></div></div></div></section>
</div>

